title: RS-25 engine installation into the Artemis II SLS Core Stage begins
summary: Aerojet Rocketdyne, an L3Harris Technologies Company, is helping install four of its RS-25 liquid-propellant rocket engines in NASA’s second Space Launch System (SLS) core stage at the agency’s Michoud Assembly Facility (MAF) in New Orleans. The beginning of installation of the upgraded former Space Shuttle Main Engines (SSME) in Core Stage-2 at MAF on Sept. 11 comes several months later than previous plans.

title: NASA Announces Summer 2023 Hottest on Record
summary: The summer of 2023 was Earth’s hottest since global records began in 1880, according to scientists at NASA’s Goddard Institute of Space Studies (GISS) in New York.

title: KaleidEO demonstrates on-orbit processing
summary: KaleidEO analyzed submeter-resolution imagery gathered by Uruguay-based Satellogic by processing data on an in-orbit computer operated by Australia’s Spiral Blue.

title: NASA Shares Unidentified Anomalous Phenomena Independent Study Report
summary: In response to a recommendation by an independent study team for NASA to play a more prominent role in understanding Unidentified Anomalous Phenomena (UAP), the agency announced Thursday it is appointing a director of UAP research.

title: BREAKING! NASA Releases Independent UAP Report "UAP Pose A Threat To US Airspace Safety"
summary: NASA Independent Study Team releases final report on Unidentified Anomalous Phenomena.

title: Space Force keeping the ‘responsive launch’ dream alive

title: Satellite industry debates size of direct-to-device market
summary: While there is growing interest in providing connectivity by satellites directly to phones, there is no consensus on how quickly that market will grow, or even what that market should be called.

title: China’s military sets up new base for space domain awareness
summary: The People’s Liberation Army has established Base 3 to improve its space domain awareness capabilities, according to a report.

title: HawkEye 360 reaches inflection point on path to profitability
summary: With a recent funding round and growing demand for its radio-frequency geolocation capabilities, HawkEye 360’s chief executive says the company has reached an “inflection point” on the path towards profitability and potentially going public.

title: SES Q&A | Leveling up multi-orbit connectivity
summary: SES is looking at other options to consolidate the space industry after merger talks with Intelsat broke down. SpaceNews interviewed newly appointed SES CEO Ruy Pinto as the multi-orbit operator prepares to receive billions of dollars in C-band clearing proceeds.
